{"type":"message","id":"3c5a23ae","parentId":"87cbc6b3","timestamp":"2026-03-01T11:19:26.582Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1434290f7737428ca69e3c90","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"lastTouchedVersion\": \"2026.2.26\",\n    \"lastTouchedAt\": \"2026-03-01T10:54:32.199Z\"\n  },\n  \"wizard\": {\n    \"lastRunAt\": \"2026-03-01T10:54:32.165Z\",\n    \"lastRunVersion\": \"2026.2.26\",\n    \"lastRunCommand\": \"doctor\",\n    \"lastRunMode\": \"local\"\n  },\n  \"auth\": {\n    \"profiles\": {\n      \"anthropic:default\": {\n        \"provider\": \"anthropic\",\n        \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n      },\n      \"moonshot:default\": {\n        \"provider\": \"moonshot\",\n        \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n      },\n      \"zai:default\": {\n        \"provider\": \"zai\",\n        \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"models\": {\n    \"mode\": \"merge\",\n    \"providers\": {\n      \"anthropic\": {\n        \"baseUrl\": \"https://api.openai-proxy.org/v1\",\n        \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n        \"models\": [\n          {\n            \"id\": \"claude-opus-4-5\",\n            \"name\": \"Claude Opus 4.5\",\n            \"reasoning\": false,\n            \"input\": [\n              \"text\",\n              \"image\"\n            ],\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"input\": 0,\n              \"output\": 0,\n              \"cacheRead\": 0,\n              \"cacheWrite\": 0\n            },\n            \"contextWindow\": 200000,\n            \"maxTokens\": 8192\n\n[181 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772363966579}}
{"type":"message","id":"0c57e4bb","parentId":"3c5a23ae","timestamp":"2026-03-01T11:19:30.961Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"让我看看 OpenClaw 的 agent 配置方式："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_36d7b36361b14cdca44698a4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --help 2>/dev/null || openclaw --help | grep -i agent"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":475,"output":42,"cacheRead":70976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71493,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772363966582}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0dc00bc","parentId":"0c57e4bb","timestamp":"2026-03-01T11:19:34.601Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_36d7b36361b14cdca44698a4","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.2.26 (bc50708) — If it works, it's automation; if it breaks, it's a \"learning opportunity.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|feishu|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|line|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3574,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.2.26 (bc50708) — If it works, it's automation; if it breaks, it's a \"learning opportunity.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|feishu|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|line|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent","cwd":"/Users/liuwei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772363974537}}
